I disagree with the above answer with a stipulation, if you understand and have done formal proofs, you should be fine but if you have not, you will be screwed because the homeworks and exams involve making runtime and correctness proofs for your algorithms. The combinatorial and probability sections of 70 are not really relevant to the class though. 

----------

If you will take 70 anyways, it's strongly recommended to take 70 prior to 170 (or at least understand Math 55 concept well). 

-----------

I think the most important material from 70 that's used for 170 are graphs. If you know the material/can self study it, then you'll be ok
